### ============================================================
### Refunds V2 — API scenarios
### Base URL: https://localhost:49609
###
### Usage:
###   1. Run "Login as admin" first — copy the token from the
###      response body into @token below.
###   2. Run scenarios in order or pick individual ones.
###   3. Replace {refundId} / {orderId} with real IDs from your
###      dev database (see seed data in Infrastructure/Database/SeedData).
### ============================================================

@baseUrl = https://localhost:49609
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN
@contentType = application/json

# ============================================================
# AUTH — obtain a JWT token
# ============================================================

### Login as admin
# Expected: 200 OK  →  { "token": "...", ... }
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/Login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "admin@admin.com",
  "password": "Admin@1234"
}

### Login as manager
# Expected: 200 OK  →  { "token": "...", ... }
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/Login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "manager@manager.com",
  "password": "Manager@1234"
}

# ============================================================
# GET /api/v2/refunds  — paged list (MaintenanceRole required)
# ============================================================

### Get all refunds — first page, default page size
# Expected: 200 OK  →  RefundListVm { refunds: [...], currentPage: 1, ... }
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get refunds — custom paging
# Expected: 200 OK
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds?pageSize=5&pageNo=1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get refunds — search by reason keyword
# Expected: 200 OK  →  filtered list
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds?search=damage&pageSize=10&pageNo=1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ============================================================
# GET /api/v2/refunds/{id}  — single refund
# ============================================================

### Get refund by id — happy path
# Expected: 200 OK  →  RefundDetailsVm { id, orderId, reason, status, items: [...] }
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get refund by id — not found
# Expected: 404 Not Found
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds/99999
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ============================================================
# POST /api/v2/refunds  — request a new refund
# ============================================================

### Request refund — happy path (replace orderId with a valid paid order id)
# Expected: 201 Created
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "orderId": 1,
  "reason": "Product arrived damaged",
  "onWarranty": true,
  "items": [
    { "productId": 1, "quantity": 1 },
    { "productId": 2, "quantity": 2 }
  ]
}

###

### Request refund — single item, no warranty
# Expected: 201 Created
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "orderId": 2,
  "reason": "Wrong item received",
  "onWarranty": false,
  "items": [
    { "productId": 3, "quantity": 1 }
  ]
}

###

### Request refund — order does not exist
# Expected: 404 Not Found  →  { "error": "Order not found." }
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "orderId": 99999,
  "reason": "Never received",
  "onWarranty": false,
  "items": [
    { "productId": 1, "quantity": 1 }
  ]
}

###

### Request refund — duplicate (run after the happy path above for same orderId)
# Expected: 409 Conflict  →  { "error": "An active refund already exists for this order." }
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "orderId": 1,
  "reason": "Duplicate attempt",
  "onWarranty": false,
  "items": [
    { "productId": 1, "quantity": 1 }
  ]
}

###

# ============================================================
# PUT /api/v2/refunds/{id}/approve  — approve (MaintenanceRole)
# ============================================================

### Approve refund — happy path (replace id with a Requested refund)
# Expected: 200 OK
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds/1/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Approve refund — not found
# Expected: 404 Not Found  →  { "error": "Refund not found." }
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds/99999/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Approve refund — already processed (run after happy path approve above)
# Expected: 409 Conflict  →  { "error": "Refund has already been processed." }
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds/1/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ============================================================
# PUT /api/v2/refunds/{id}/reject  — reject (MaintenanceRole)
# ============================================================

### Reject refund — happy path (use a different Requested refund, e.g. id=2)
# Expected: 200 OK
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds/2/reject
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Reject refund — not found
# Expected: 404 Not Found  →  { "error": "Refund not found." }
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds/99999/reject
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Reject refund — already processed (run after happy path reject above)
# Expected: 409 Conflict  →  { "error": "Refund has already been processed." }
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds/2/reject
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ============================================================
# Authorization boundary checks
# ============================================================

### Get list without token — should be blocked
# Expected: 401 Unauthorized
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds

###

### Approve without admin/manager/service role (login as regular user first)
# Expected: 403 Forbidden
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/refunds/1/approve
Authorization: Bearer <regular-user-token>

###
